nals]]''\n| [[Ajak]]\n| Post-production\n|-\n| {{TBA}}\n| ''[[Bliss (upcoming film)|Bliss]]''\n| Isabel\n| Post-production\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''Un Nuevo Amanecer''\n| Fabiola\n| Spanish-language [[telenovela]]\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Teresa (1989 TV series)|Teresa]]''\n| Teresa\n| Spanish-language telenovela\n|-\n| 1992\n| ''[[Dream On (TV series)|Dream On]]''\n| Carmela\n| October 10; episode \"Domestic Bliss\"\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''[[The Sinbad Show]]''\n| Gloria Contreras\n| [[Recurring character]]\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 1994\n| ''[[Roadracers]]''\n| Donna\n|\n|-\n| ''[[El vuelo del \u00e1guila]]''\n| Juana Cata\n| Spanish-language telenovela\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 1997\n| ''[[The Hunchback (1997 film)|The Hunchback]]''\n| [[Esmeralda (The Hunchback of Notre-Dame)|Esmeralda]]\n| Nominated\u2013[[ALMA Award|ALMA Award for Outstanding Individual Performance in a Made-for-Television Movie or Mini-Series in a Crossover Role]]\n|-\n| ''Gente Bien''\n| Teresa\n| Guest star; Spanish-language telenovela\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Action (TV series)|Action]]''\n| Herself\n| Re-Enter the Dragon<br />Guest star\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[In the Time of the Butterflies (film)|In the Time of the Butterflies]]''\n| [[Mirabal sisters|Minerva Mirabal]]\n| Producer; feature<br />[[ALMA Award|ALMA Award for Outstanding Actor/Actress in a Made for Television Movie or Miniseries]]<br />Nominated\u2013[[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Actress in a Movie/Miniseries|Broadcast Film Critics Association Award for Best Actress in a Picture Made for Television]]\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2003\n| ''The Maldonado Miracle''\n|\n| Feature; producer, director. [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing For A Children's Series|Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Directing in a Children/Youth/Family Special]]\n|-\n| ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''\n| Guest host\n| March 15\n|-\n| 2006\u20132010\n| ''[[Ugly Betty]]''\n| Sofia Reyes / Nurse in Telenovela\n| Executive producer (85 episodes) and guest star<br />with 15 cameo episodes <br />Nominated\u2013[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Guest Actress in a Comedy Series]] (2007)<br />Nominated\u2013[[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Comedy Series]] (2007)<br />Nominated\u2013[[Producers Guild of America Award for Best Episodic Comedy]] (2007)\n|-\n| 2009\u20132013\n| ''[[30 Rock]]''\n| Elisa Pedrera\n| 7 episodes<br />Guest star\n|}\n\n==Event appearances==\n* A member of the [[2005 Cannes Film Festival]] jury.<ref>{{cite news |title=Cannes festival opens with drama |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/4533671.stm |work=BBC News |date=May 11, 2005}}</ref>\n* Co-hosted the annual [[Nobel Peace Prize Concert]] with [[Julianne Moore]] in [[Oslo]], [[Norway]] on December 11, 2005.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1145227,00.html |title=People: Jan. 9, 2006 |work=Time |date=January 1, 2006 |first=Rebecca |last=Winters Keegan}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n{{Portalbar|Hispanic and Latino Americans}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist\n| colwidth   = 30em\n| refs       = \n{{cite web\n| title      = Salma Hayek Biography (1966?\u2013)\n| publisher  = FilmReference.com\n| url        = http://www.filmreference.com/film/83/Salma-Hayek\n| accessdate = February 19, 2008\n}}<ref name=\"People-Bio\">\n{{cite web\n| title      = Salma Hayek Biography\n| work       = People\n| url        = http://www.people.com/people/salma_hayek/biography/0,,20007809_10,00.html\n| accessdate = August 9, 2010\n}}\n</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n {{commons}}\n {{wikiquote}}\n* {{IMDb name}}\n* {{Amg name}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hayek, Salma}}\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Activists from California]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Veracruz]]\n[[Category:American cosmetics businesspeople]]\n[[Category:American 