.com/strang.htm ''\"God Has Made Us a Kingdom\" James Strang and the Midwest Mormon'']. [[Signature Books]].\n* {{cite book\n | last       = Talmage\n | first      = James E.\n | authorlink = James E. Talmage\n | title      = [[The House of the Lord: A Study of Holy Sanctuaries, Ancient and Modern]]\n | location   = Salt Lake City, Utah\n | publisher  = [[Signature Books]]\n | origyear   = 1912\n | year       = 1998\n | isbn       = 1-56085-114-7\n }}.\n* {{Cite conference |last= Tvedtnes |first= John A. |title= Early Christian and Jewish Rituals Related to Temple Practices |url= http://www.fairmormon.org/perspectives/fair-conferences/1999-fair-conference/1999-early-christian-and-jewish-rituals-related-to-temple-practices |conference= FAIR Conference |conference-url= http://www.fairmormon.org/perspectives/fair-conferences |year= 1999 |location= Ben Lomond, California |publisher= [[FairMormon]] |ref= harv}}\n* {{cite book\n | title      = Preparing to Enter the Holy Temple\n | year       = 2002\n | publisher  = LDS Church\n | url        = https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/manual/preparing-to-enter-the-holy-temple/preparing-to-enter-the-holy-temple?lang=eng\n }}.\n* \"[http://www.bbc.co.uk/religion/religions/mormon/customs/temple.shtml The Temple]\" British Broadcasting [[BBC]], 2005-11-09. Article on Mormon temple worship from BBC Religion & Ethics website, last accessed 2006-09-19.\n{{Refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{Citation\n | last=Barber\n | first=Allen\n | title=Celestial Symbols: Symbolism in Doctrine, Religious Traditions and Temple Architecture\n | publisher=Cedar Fort\n | year=2006\n | isbn=0-88290-808-1\n}}\n* [[Richard O. Cowan|Cowan, Richard O.]], ''Temples to Dot the Earth'', January 1997, {{ISBN|1-55517-339-X}}\n*{{Citation\n | last=Greene\n | first=Mark\n | title=The Scriptural Temple\n | publisher=Cedar Fort\n | year=2000\n | isbn=0-88290-681-X\n}}\n*{{Citation\n | last=King\n | first=David\n | title=Come to the House of the 